# SSR, Prefetch & HydrateClient

## Page (Server Component)

```tsx
import { prefetch, trpc, HydrateClient } from "@/src/trpc/server";
import TextToSpeechView from "@/src/feature/text-to-speech/views/text-to-speech-view";

export const metadata: Metadata = { title: "Text to AI Voice" };

export default async function Page({ searchParams }: { searchParams: Promise<{...}> }) {
  prefetch(trpc.voices.getAll.queryOptions());

  return (
    <HydrateClient>
      <TextToSpeechView />
    </HydrateClient>
  );
}
```

## View (Client — consumes cache)

```tsx
"use client";
const trpc = useTRPC();
const { data: voices } = useSuspenseQuery(trpc.voices.getAll.queryOptions());
```

## Rules

- Prefetch every query the view will `useSuspenseQuery` — same `queryOptions(...)` args.
- Always wrap the client view in `<HydrateClient>` after prefetch.
- Prefer `useSuspenseQuery` / `useSuspenseQueries` over `useQuery` + loading flags.
- Do not `fetch` in `useEffect` for SSR data.
- Root metadata uses `title.template`; pages export only `{ title: "Segment" }`.
- Layouts may prefetch shared queries (e.g. billing) once for children.
- For URL filters: parse with nuqs (`*SearchParamsCache.parse`) before prefetch — see `nuqs-url-state.mdc`.
